@startuml DCC_Application_Class_Diagram

title Class Diagram - Dummy Coordination Conversion (DCC) Application

package "Client" {
  class CoordinateConverterGUI {
    + void displayGUI()
    + void handleUserInput()
    + void displayCoordinateGroups(List<CoordinateGroup>)
    + void showConversionResults(CartesianCoordinate, PolarCoordinate)
  }

  class CoordinateManager {
    + void createCoordinateGroup(CartesianCoordinate)
    + void createCoordinateGroup(PolarCoordinate)
    + List<CoordinateGroup> retrieveAllCoordinateGroups()
    + CoordinateGroup retrieveCoordinateGroup(String label)
    + void updateCoordinateGroup(CoordinateGroup)
    + void deleteCoordinateGroup(Integer id)
  }

  class DCCService {
    + void sendRequest(String request)
    + String getResponse()
  }
}

package "Server" {
  interface Database {
    + void storeCoordinateGroup(CoordinateGroup)
    + CoordinateGroup retrieveCoordinateGroup(Integer id)
    + List<CoordinateGroup> retrieveAllCoordinateGroups()
    + void updateCoordinateGroup(CoordinateGroup)
    + void deleteCoordinateGroup(Integer id)
  }

  class MySQLDatabase implements Database {
    + void connect()
    + void disconnect()
  }

  class Server {
    + void startListening()
    + void processRequest(String request)
    + void sendResponse(String response)
  }
}

package "Common" {
  class CoordinateGroup {
    - Integer id
    - String label
    - Date timestamp
    - CartesianCoordinate cartesian
    - PolarCoordinate polar
  }

  class CartesianCoordinate {
    - Double x
    - Double y
  }

  class PolarCoordinate {
    - Double r
    - Double theta
  }
}

' Associations
CoordinateConverterGUI --> CoordinateManager : Uses
CoordinateManager --> DCCService : Communicates with
DCCService --> Server : Sends requests to
Server --> MySQLDatabase : Persists data to
MySQLDatabase --> CoordinateGroup : Stores and manages

@enduml